CITI on JSW Steel

Sell, TP Rs 1165

At Rs92.5bn (7% ahead), adj. 4Q EBITDA rose 43% yoy; higher India volumes (+8%) & realizations (+5%), costs flattish.

Adj. India EBITDA/t: Rs11,620 vs. Rs8,790 in 3Q, Rs8,930 last year.

Net D/EBITDA: 1.8x (BPSL slump sale) vs. 2.9x as of Dec25.

Call highlights:

1) merger with BMM Ispat, 0.9mt longs;

2) divestment of Bhushan Power effective 27 March—reduction in JSTL net debt of ~Rs370bn (Rs295bn in Mar26);

3) JSTL announced another 5mt in Vijayanagar—capacity to rise from ~30mt to 49mt by FY30;

4) HRC prices rose by Rs2,000/t in Apr, Rs1,000 in May; mgmt expects range-bound pricing;

5) 1QFY27 costs should rise by Rs3,000/t. EBITDA/t has upside potential from 4Q; however, at 9.3x EV/EBITDA, this appears priced in.
